18/06/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- On Tuesday (17 June), Parliament Speaker Servet Pellumbi met with Marion Hoffmann, the UN High Commissioner for Refugees representative in Albania.
Pellumbi stressed that the government is working to boost human rights co-operation, adding that parliament would soon discuss a bill on integration of refugees.
In turn, Hoffmann praised Albania's role in dealing with the Kosovo and Macedonia crises involving the rights of ethnic minorities.
(ATA, BBC - 17/06/03)
